					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uglyflower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1741178); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1741178&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163883" alt="UglyFlower" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1741178)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uglyflower" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1741178); return false;" >UglyFlower</a></span> <span class="odate time_1385014685 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Nov 2013 06:18</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1897745">
									

<p>A few issues with grammar, for example the last line uses the word tinny instead of tiny. I wasn't sure if I should change that incase you wanted the word tinny to describe a robot voice or something. A few issues with the way sentences are structured. for example: &quot;Before he could place the torch to metal a hand placed itself on his shoulder.&quot; needs a comma between &quot;metal&quot; and &quot;a&quot;.</p>
<p>&quot;A single sentence, spoken in a tinny voice. Something no doubt meant for the dying Manager.&quot; This can easily be one sentence rather than two that sound confusing together.</p>
<p>For example it might sound better as, &quot;A tiny voice uttered a single sentence which was undoubtedly directed towards the dying manager&quot;</p>
<p>There are more issues similar to these, but I'm too exhausted to go over them right now.</p>
<p>Altogether I enjoyed it.</p>

							</div>

								
